  "ChefNotify": "The <#d6d6ff>Chef</color> got you some {0}!\\nThis caused you to have <#ffff00>{1}</color>",
  "ChefRotten": "diarrhea",
  "ChefRottenSuffix": "<#ffa500>You must</color> <#ffff00>kill or vent</color> <#ffa500>within</color> <b>{0}</b>s",
  "Clairvoyant": "Clairvoyant",
  "ClairvoyantInfo": "Know Remaining Killer Counts",
  "ClairvoyantInfoLong": "(<#8cffff>Crewmates</color>):\n<size=80%>Know exactly how many killers remain — just by venting.\n_____________________________________\nDifficulty: ★☆☆☆☆\n\n[Skills]\n・<b><color=#8cffff>Enemy Count</color></b>\nVent or pet to see the current count of surviving Impostors and Neutral Killers.\n\n<i>Knowledge is the first weapon.</i></size>",
  "Cleanser": "Cleanser",
  "CleanserInfo": "Erase All Addons of your vote target",
  "CleanserInfoLong": "(<#8cffff>Crewmates</color>):\n<size=80%>Vote a player to strip them of all their add-ons.\n_____________________________________\nDifficulty: ★★☆☆☆\n\n[Skills]\n・<b><color=#8cffff>Cleanse</color></b>\nVote for a target in a meeting to remove all their add-ons after the meeting ends. Depending on settings, cleansed players may never receive add-ons again.\n\n<i>Back to basics.</i></size>",
  "CleanserRemoveSelf": "You can not cleanse yourself",
  "CleanserRemovedRole": "<b>{0}</b> has been cleansed. All their Addons will be removed after the meeting.",
  "Convener": "Convener",
  "ConvenerInfo": "Teleport Everyone To You",
  "ConvenerInfoLong": "(<#8cffff>Crewmates</color>):\n<size=80%>Teleport everyone on the ship to your location.\n_____________________________________\nDifficulty: ★★☆☆☆\n\n[Skills]\n・<b><color=#8cffff>Mass Teleport</color></b>\nVent or pet to instantly teleport every player to your current position.\n\n<i>If the mountain won't come to you...</i></size>",
  "CopyCat": "Copycat",
  "CopyCatInfo": "Use kill button to copy target's role",
  "CopyCatInfoLong": "(<#8cffff>Crewmates</color>):\n<size=80%>Use your kill button to copy another crewmate's role.\n_____________________________________\nDifficulty: ★★★☆☆\n\n[Skills]\n・<b><color=#8cffff>Imitation</color></b>\nPress your kill button to copy the target's role. Only some crewmate roles can be copied. Attempting to copy non-crew or a Rascal may kill them instead (host-controlled). You cannot guess, and too many miscopies lead to suicide.\n\n<i>Flattery may be the sincerest form of survival.</i></size>",
  "CopyCatAlreadyCopy": "You have already copied a role in this round",
  "CopyCatCanKill": "CopyCat can kill when miscopy",
  "CopyCatCanNotCopy": "You can not copy the target's role",
  "CopyCatCopyCooldown": "Copy cooldown",
  "CopyCatMiscopyLimit": "Number of miscopy until suicide",
  "CopyCatResetToCopyCatEachRound": "Reset role to <#ffb2ab>Copycat</color> after each meeting",
  "CopyCatRoleChange": "Your role has been changed to <b>{0}</b>",
  "Coroner": "Coroner",
  "CoronerInfo": "Find corpses and their killers",
  "CoronerInfoLong": "(<#8cffff>Crewmates</color>):\n<size=80%>The dead speak. Let them guide you to the killer.\n_____________________________________\nDifficulty: ★★★☆☆\n\n[Skills]\n・<b><color=#8cffff>Crime Scene Tracking</color></b>\nWhen you try to report a corpse, instead of reporting it, an arrow pointing toward the killer appears. The arrow disappears when a meeting is called.\n\n<i>The answer is always left at the scene.</i></size>",
  "CoronerArrowsPointingToDeadBody": "Arrows pointing to dead bodies",
  "CoronerKillerNotify": "The <color=#8B0000>Coroner</color> has an arrow pointing toward you!",
  "CoronerLeaveDeadBodyUnreportable": "Bodies the <color=#8B0000>Coroner</color> uses can't be reported",
  "CoronerNoTrack": "Nothing to track",
  "CoronerNotifyKiller": "Notify Killer about being Tracked",
  "CoronerTrackRecorded": "Track recorded",
  "CrewmateEndKnot": "Crewmate",
  "CrewmateEndKnotInfo": "Do your tasks",
  "CrewmateEndKnotInfoLong": "(<#8cffff>Crewmates</color>):\n<size=80%>Find the Impostors and complete your tasks.\n_____________________________________\nDifficulty: ★☆☆☆☆\n\n[Skills]\n・<b><color=#8cffff>Tasks</color></b>\nComplete tasks to help your team win. Eject all killers or finish all tasks to claim victory.\n\n<i>Simple in theory. Trickier in practice.</i></size>",
  "Crusader": "Crusader",
  "CrusaderInfo": "Kill a player's attacker",
  "CrusaderInfoLong": "(<#8cffff>Crewmates</color>):\n<size=80%>Protect a player — and strike down whoever dares attack them.\n_____________________________________\nDifficulty: ★★☆☆☆\n\n[Skills]\n・<b><color=#8cffff>Crusade</color></b>\nUse your kill button to crusade a player. If that player is then attacked, you kill their attacker instead.\n\n<i>Attack the crusaded, and face the crusader.</i></size>",
  "CrusaderKillButtonText": "Crusade",
  "CrusaderSkillCooldown": "Crusade Cooldown",
  "CrusaderSkillLimit": "Maximum Crusades",
  "Dad": "Dad",
  "DadInfo": "You're that iconic dad....",
  "DadInfoLong": "(<#8cffff>Crewmates</color>):\n<size=80%>Survive on alcohol — gather money, buy beer, unlock abilities.\n_____________________________________\nDifficulty: ★★★★★\n\n[Skills]\n・<b><color=#8cffff>Alcohol Level</color></b>\nYour alcohol level (‰) decreases over time and when attacked or ejected. Earn money by completing tasks and buy beer at the shop vent. Hit 0‰ and you die.\n\n・<b><color=#8cffff>7 Unlockable Abilities</color></b>\n<size=70%>Switch with pet, activate by venting:\n- Going for Milk: TP outside map; return with milk for instant crew win\n- Super Vision: Maximum vision briefly\n- Sniffing: Arrows to all dead bodies\n- Sleep: Immune to interactions; alcohol stable\n- Rage: Kill the next player you see\n- Giving Drink: Force nearby players to reveal roles next meeting\n- God of Alcohol: Reset to 1‰; alcohol increases from now on\nEach ability (except Milk) reduces your alcohol on use.</size>\n\n<i>Keep it steady. Keep it cold. Keep it flowing.</i></size>",
  "Dad.Ability.BecomeGodOfAlcohol": "Becoming God Of Alcohol",
  "Dad.Ability.GiveDrink": "Giving Drink",
  "Dad.Ability.GoForMilk": "Going For Milk",
  "Dad.Ability.Rage": "Raging",
  "Dad.Ability.Sleep": "Sleeping",
  "Dad.Ability.Sniffing": "Sniffing",
