  ============================== */
  "Mode": "Mode",
  "GameMode": "Game Mode",
  "GameModeListTitle": "Game Modes",
  "DoingTasksIsPointlessInThisGameMode": "Look, I see that you're a very diligent crewmate, but....\\nDoing tasks is completely pointless in this game mode",
  "NToCheckGameModeSettings": "Type <b>/n</b> to view the settings for this game mode",
  // Standard
  "Standard": "Standard",
  "ModeStandard": "Gamemode: Standard",
  // Bedwars
  "BedWars": "BED WARS",
  "ModeBedWars": "Gamemode: Bed Wars",
  "ModeDescribe.BedWars": "In the Bed Wars gamemode, players are split into teams. Each team has a bed. If a team's bed is destroyed, all players in that team can no longer respawn. The goal is to destroy all other teams' beds (via Pet button) and be the last team alive.\\n\\nYou can buy items (blocks, weapons, tool, etc.) and team upgrades (heal pool, haste, trap, etc.) in shops from the resources (iron, gold, diamond, emerald) you can collect from the generators on the map. These are useful for protecting the bed with various layers to make it harder to break it, increase your attack damage, increase your defense, or give you or your team various abilities.\\n\\nIn the beginning, there's a grace period, where no attacks are allowed, and players can't leave their own base.\\n\\nEach player has an inventory with all of their items. Cycle through the slots using the Vanish button or by typing the number of the slot in the chat (ex. '5'). Use weapons through the kill button, other items via Pet. To start breaking someone's bed, Pet. Make sure to always have the correct item selected in your inventory (blocks when you protect the bed, tools when you break beds, etc.).\\nYou can break beds with anything, but using the correct tool for each layer will make the process significantly faster.\\n\\nIf you die, you will respawn after a few seconds, unless your bed is broken. If your bed is broken, you will not respawn anymore.",
