  // Hot Potato - HP
  "HotPotato": "HOT POTATO",
  "ModeHotPotato": "Gamemode: Hot Potato",
  "ModeDescribe.HotPotato": "In the Hot Potato gamemode, one player always has the hot potato, and they can pass it to anyone by going near someone. Each X seconds (X is set by the host), the player who holds the hot potato dies. The last player alive wins!\\n\\nNote: You cannot pass the hot potato to the player that just gave it to you (their name is colored in cyan, it means they cannot get the hot potato) unless there are only 2 players left.",
  "GameModeTutorial.HotPotato": "<size=90%>The current game mode is <#e8cd46>Hot Potato</color>.</size>\\n<size=80%>The person with a black name holds the hot potato.\\nThey can pass it to someone by going near them.\\nThe previous holder's name is colored in cyan, they cannot regain\\nthe hot potato until someone else got it, unless only 2 players remain.\\nWhen the time limit ends, the holder of the hot potato dies, and the timer resets,\\nthe hot potato is assigned to a random player. Be the last player alive to win!</size>",
  "HotPotato_ExtraTimeOnAirship": "Extra Time on <color=#ed0007>Airship</color>",
  "HotPotato_ExtraTimeOnFungle": "Extra Time on <color=#ffa646>Fungle</color>",
  "HotPotato_HolderCanPassViaKillButton": "Holders Pass The Potato Via Kill Button Instead Of Proximity",
  "HotPotato_HolderHasArrowToNearestPlayerIfPlayersLessThan": "Holder Has an Arrow to the Nearest Player If the Remaining Players Is Less Than",
  "HotPotato_HolderSpeed": "Speed of the Player Holding the Hot Potato",
  "HotPotato_HoldingNotify": "<#ffff00><size=2>You hold the Hot Potato! Pass it or die!</size></color>",
  "HotPotato_Range": "Pass Range",
  "HotPotato_Time": "The Holder of the Hot Potato is Killed Every",
  "HotPotato_TimeLeftSuffix": "Kill in ",
  // King Of The Zones - KOTZ
  "KingOfTheZones": "KING OF THE ZONES",
  "ModeKingOfTheZones": "Gamemode: King Of The Zones",
  "ModeDescribe.KingOfTheZones": "In the King Of The Zones gamemode, players are split into teams. Some rooms on the map represent a zone. If a team has more players in a room than all other teams, they control the zone. Every second, each team gets 1 point for each zone controlled. Gain as many points as possible, since the team with the highest score wins!\\n\\nPlayers can tag others using the kill button. Tagged players are teleported outside of the map for a few seconds, then teleport back.\\n\\nDepending on the settings, zones may move during the game. If so, this will be indicated by a timer. When a zone moves, it may have a downtime. This is the case if the timer is gray.",
  "KOTZ.EndScreen.Statistics": "Points: <#ffff44>{0}</color>",
  "KOTZ.EndScreen.Winner.Blue": "The Blue Team wins!",
  "KOTZ.EndScreen.Winner.Green": "The Green Team wins!",
  "KOTZ.EndScreen.Winner.Orange": "The Orange Team wins!",
  "KOTZ.EndScreen.Winner.Red": "The Red Team wins!",
  "KOTZ.EndScreen.Winner.Rose": "The Rose Team wins!",
  "KOTZ.EndScreen.Winner.Tan": "The Tan Team wins!",
  "KOTZ.EndScreen.Winner.Yellow": "The Yellow Team wins!",
  "KOTZ.Notify.AssignedToTeam.Blue": "<#ffffff>You are in the </color>Blue Team",
  "KOTZ.Notify.AssignedToTeam.Green": "<#ffffff>You are in the </color>Green Team",
  "KOTZ.Notify.AssignedToTeam.Orange": "<#ffffff>You are in the </color>Orange Team",
  "KOTZ.Notify.AssignedToTeam.Red": "<#ffffff>You are in the </color>Red Team",
  "KOTZ.Notify.AssignedToTeam.Rose": "<#ffffff>You are in the </color>Rose Team",
  "KOTZ.Notify.AssignedToTeam.Tan": "<#ffffff>You are in the </color>Tan Team",
  "KOTZ.Notify.AssignedToTeam.Yellow": "<#ffffff>You are in the </color>Yellow Team",
  "KOTZ.Notify.ShortIntro": "Welcome to another game of <#ff0000>King Of The Zones</color>!\\n<size=90%><#ffff44>{0}</color> teams, <#ffff44>{1}</color> zones.\\nTag cooldown: <#ffff44>{2}</color>s, Respawn time: <#ffff44>{3}</color>s.</size>\\nGood luck and have fun!",
  "KOTZ.Notify.Tutorial.Basics": "We're playing <#ff0000>King Of The Zones</color>.\\n<size=90%>Players are split into <#ffff44>{0}</color> teams.\\n<#ffff44>{1}</color> rooms on the map represent a zone.\\nTeams must have majority (by player count) in a zone to control it,\\nwhich is awarded by 1 point for each zone every second.</size>",
  "KOTZ.Notify.Tutorial.GameEnd.PointsOnly": "<size=90%>When a team reaches <#ffff44>{0}</color> points, the game ends and they win.\\n<size=70%>Upon a tie, the game ends when the tie breaks.</size></size>",
  "KOTZ.Notify.Tutorial.GameEnd.PointsOrTime": "<size=90%>The game ends if a team reaches <#ffff44>{0}</color> points or after <#ffff44>{1}m {2}s</color>.\\nWhen there's no tie, the team with the most points wins.</size>",
  "KOTZ.Notify.Tutorial.GameEnd.TimeOnly": "<size=90%>After <#ffff44>{0} minutes and {1} seconds</color>, the team with the most points wins.\\n<size=70%>Upon a tie, the game ends when the tie breaks.</size></size>",
  "KOTZ.Notify.Tutorial.Tagging": "<size=90%>Players can tag others using the kill button (cooldown: <#ffff44>{0}</color>s),\\nwhich teleports them outside the map for <#ffff44>{1}</color>s.</size>",
  "KOTZ.Notify.Tutorial.ZonesMoving.AllAtOnce": "<size=90%>Every <#ffff44>{0}</color>s, all zones move to a different room.\\n(Indicated by timers next to the room names.)</size>",
  "KOTZ.Notify.Tutorial.ZonesMoving.Downtime": "<size=90%>After a zone has moved, it stays neutral for <#ffff44>{0}</color>s,\\nmeaning no teams can have majority in it.\\n(Indicated by a gray timer.)</size>",
  "KOTZ.Notify.Tutorial.ZonesMoving.Separately": "<size=90%>Every <#ffff44>{0}</color>s, a zone moves to a different room.\\n(Indicated by timers next to the room names.)</size>",
  "KOTZ.PNTO.Less": "Less Teams",
  "KOTZ.PNTO.More": "More Teams",
  "KOTZ.Suffix.PointsToWin": "First to <#ffff44>{0}</color> points wins",
  "KOTZ.Suffix.RespawnTime": "<#ff0000>DEAD</color> <#888888>-</color> RESPAWNING IN <#ffff44>{0}</color>",
  "KOTZ.Suffix.SpawnProtectionTime": "<#00ffa5>Under Spawn Protection</color> <#888888>-</color> <#ffff44>{0}</color>",
  "KOTZ.Suffix.Tie": "Tie: {0}\\nWaiting for the tie to break....",
  "KOTZ.SuffixHelp.GameEndTimer": "<size=80%>Game End Timer: </size>",
  "KOTZ.SuffixHelp.Points": "<size=80%>Points: </size>",
  "KOTZ.SuffixHelp.Zones.Plural": "<size=80%>Zones: </size>",
  "KOTZ.SuffixHelp.Zones.Single": "<size=80%>Zone: </size>",
  "KingOfTheZones.AllZonesMoveAtOnce": "All Zones Move At Once  (if disabled, there will be an equal gap between zone movements)",
  "KingOfTheZones.AutoSetNumTeams": "Set the Number of Teams Automatically based on the Player Count  (If the below setting doesn't produce even teams)",
  "KingOfTheZones.DowntimeAfterZoneMove": "Downtime After Zone Move  (during downtime, the zone stays neutral)",
  "KingOfTheZones.GameEndsByPoints": "Game Ends If a Team Gets to a Certain Amount of Points",
  "KingOfTheZones.GameEndsByTimeLimit": "Game Ends After a Certain Time",
  "KingOfTheZones.MaxGameLength": "Maximum Game Length",
  "KingOfTheZones.NumTeams": "Number of Teams",
  "KingOfTheZones.NumZones": "Number of Zones",
  "KingOfTheZones.PointsToWin": "Points to Win",
  "KingOfTheZones.PreferNumTeams": "Prefer",
  "KingOfTheZones.RespawnTime": "Respawn Time",
  "KingOfTheZones.SpawnProtectionTime": "Spawn Protection Time",
  "KingOfTheZones.TagCooldown": "Tag Cooldown",
  "KingOfTheZones.ZoneMoveTime": "Zones Move Every",
  "KingOfTheZones.ZonesMove": "Zones Move",
  // Mingle
  "Mingle": "MINGLE",
  "ModeMingle": "Gamemode: Mingle",
  "ModeDescribe.Mingle": "In the Mingle gamemode, the game assigns a certain number of players to certain rooms on the map. At the end of the time limit, exactly that number of players need to be in the rooms. If there are too many or too few players in a room, all players in that room die. If you are not in any of the assigned rooms, you die. Oh, and if no one dies in a round, the time limit permanently decreases. The last player alive wins!",
  "Mingle.Tutorial": "The current game mode is <#FE9900>Mingle</color>.\\n<size=90%>The game assigns a certain number of players to certain rooms on the map.\\nAt the end of the time limit, exactly those numbers of players need to be in the rooms.\\nIf there are too many or too few players in a room, all players in that room die.\\nIf you are not in any of the assigned rooms, you die.\\nOh, and if no one dies in a round, the time limit permanently decreases.\\nThe last player alive wins!</size>",
  "Mingle.DisplayCurrentPlayerCountInEachRoomOption": "Display Current Player Count in Each Room",
  "Mingle.ExtraTimeOnAirshipOption": "Extra Time on <#ed0007>Airship</color>",
  "Mingle.ExtraTimeOnFungleOption": "Extra Time on <#ffa646>Fungle</color>",
  "Mingle.MaxRequiredPlayersPerRoomOption": "Maximum Required Players Per Room",
  "Mingle.MaxWinningPlayersOption": "Maximum Winning Players",
  "Mingle.MinTimeOption": "Minimum Time Limit",
  "Mingle.NotInRequiredRoom": "Not in any assigned room",
  "Mingle.TimeDecreaseOnNoDeathOption": "Time Decrease on No Death",
  "Mingle.TimeLimitOption": "Starting Time Limit",
  // Natural Disasters - ND
  "NaturalDisasters": "NATURAL DISASTERS",
  "ModeNaturalDisasters": "Gamemode: Natural Disasters",
  "ModeDescribe.NaturalDisasters": "In the Natural Disasters gamemode, the map is filled with natural disasters. You have to survive them all and be the last player alive to win!\\n\\n<size=80%>List of all Natural Disasters and their effects:</size><size=70%>\\n- Earthquake: The ground shakes, making it hard to move.\\n- Meteor: A meteor falls from the sky, killing players in a certain range.\\n- Volcano Eruption: Lava flows from one spot, killing players.\\n- Tornado: Players are sucked into the tornado and die.\\n- Thunderstorm: Lightning strikes outside of rooms, killing players that it hits.\\n- Sandstorm: Sand blows, making it hard to see.\\n- Tsunami: A giant wave comes moving in a specific direction, drowning players that are on the way.\\n- Sinkhole: The ground collapses, killing players in range and any players that enter this range in the future.\\n- Building Collapse: A building on the ship collapses, killing everyone inside it. Collapsed rooms cannot be entered in the future.</size>",
  "GameModeTutorial.NaturalDisasters": "<size=90%>The current game mode is <#03fc4a>Natural Disasters</color>.</size>\\n<size=80%>Various disasters will constantly spawn on the map.\\nSome kill you instantly, some just debuff you temporarily.\\nBe the last player alive to win!</size>",
  "CollapsedBuildings": "<#03fc4a>Collapsed Buildings:</color> {0}",
  "AvailableBuildings": "<#03FCFC>Available Buildings:</color> {0}",
  "ND_BuildingCollapse": "Building Collapse",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-0.Collapsed": "It was like in the movies, right? You know, when the building collapses and everyone dies!",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-0.Drowned": "You said you were thirsty, right? Here's some water!",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-0.Lava": "Lava is not the best place to swim, huh?",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-0.Lightning": "You've been.... THUNDERSTRUCK!",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-0.Meteor": "Meteor.... I hardly knew her!",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-0.Sunken": "Did you know that the Titanic was sunk by a sinkhole? Well, now you do!",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-0.Tornado": "Out for a spin? I hope this tornado didn't make you dizzy!",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-1.Collapsed": "Wow! You really brought the house down with you!",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-1.Drowned": "Guess you finally learnt how to sink or swim.... mostly sink!",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-1.Lava": "Careful! That's not a hot tub!",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-1.Lightning": "That really brightened your day, huh?",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-1.Meteor": "Look on the bright side: you made history!",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-1.Sunken": "Down you go! Hope you enjoyed the trip!",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-1.Tornado": "Wheeeee! Hope you enjoyed the ride!",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-2.Collapsed": "Next time, maybe don't stand under the collapsing part!",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-2.Drowned": "Breathing is optional, right?",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-2.Lava": "Ooooh, toasty! Just how you like it?",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-2.Lightning": "I'd say that was electrifying!",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-2.Meteor": "You really took \"out of this world\" to heart!",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-2.Sunken": "Don't worry, it's cozy down there.... probably!",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-2.Tornado": "That must've been a dizzying experience!",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-3.Collapsed": "Don't worry, I'm sure that building needed a hug!",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-3.Drowned": "You really went all in on that swimming lesson!",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-3.Lava": "You didn't think it was THAT hot, did you?",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-3.Lightning": "You should try standing somewhere LESS shiny next time!",
  "ND_DRLaughMessage-3.Meteor": "Oops! Right place, wrong time!",
