  "Mission.Vote": "Get voted 2+ times",
  "Mission.AllTaskComp": "Complete all tasks",
  "Mission.Report": "Report a dead body",
  "MissioneerSelectMission": "Vote for a player to accept their mission:",
  "MissioneerNoMissions": "No missions available this meeting",
  "MissioneerMissionSet": "Mission set: {0}",
  "MissioneerInvalidTarget": "That player has no mission for you",
  "MissioneerSelectingHint": "Vote a player to accept their mission (or vote yourself to cancel)",
  "MissioneerSelfVoteHint": "Vote yourself to see available missions",
  "MissioneerTarget": "Target",
  "MissioneerRoom": "Room",

  "JackalHadouHo": "Wave Cannon Jackal",
  "JackalHadouHoInfo": "Charge and fire a directional wave cannon with the Phantom button; recruit a Tama and consume it for a super beam",
  "JackalHadouHoInfoLong": "(<#00b4eb>Jackal</color>):\n<size=80%>Charge and fire a directional wave cannon — and recruit a Tama to unleash a devastating super beam.\n_____________________________________\nDifficulty: ★★★★☆\n\n[Skills]\n・<b><color=#00b4eb>Wave Cannon</color></b>\nPress the Phantom (vanish) button to charge a beam. After the charge and warning phases, the beam fires forward in your facing direction, killing anyone in its path.\n\n・<b><color=#00b4eb>Tama Recruitment</color></b>\nDuring a meeting, vote yourself to enter sidekick assignment mode, then vote a target to mark them as a candidate. After the meeting, approach within 1.5 tiles for 1.5 seconds to convert them into your Tama.\n\n・<b><color=#00b4eb>Super Beam</color></b>\nWhen the Tama uses their Kill button on you, you are loaded. Your next Phantom press fires a super beam — thicker and with a longer charge — which consumes the Tama on firing.\n\n<i>Full power. Fire.</i></size>",
  "JackalHadouHoDirectionDetectDuration": "Aim Window",
  "JackalHadouHoChargeTime": "Normal Charge Duration",
  "JackalHadouHoSuperChargeTime": "Super Charge Duration",
  "JackalHadouHoWarningTime": "Warning Phase Duration",
  "JackalHadouHoFiringTime": "Firing Phase Duration",
  "JackalHadouHoBeamThickness": "Normal Beam Thickness",
  "JackalHadouHoSuperBeamThickness": "Super Beam Thickness",
  "JackalHadouHoSelfDestruct": "Self-Destruct on Miss",
  "JackalHadouHoKillJackal": "Beam Kills Jackal Team",
  "JackalHadouHoBeamColorMode": "Beam Color Mode",
  "JackalHadouHoBeamColorRainbow": "Rainbow",
  "JackalHadouHoBeamColorSingle": "Single",
  "JackalHadouHoCanMakeSidekick": "Can Recruit Tama",
  "JackalHadouHoSidekickCooldown": "Tama Recruit Cooldown",
  "JackalHadouHoSkModeOn": "Sidekick mode ON. Vote a candidate (vote self again to cancel).",
  "JackalHadouHoSkModeOff": "Sidekick mode canceled.",
  "JackalHadouHoSkInvalid": "That player cannot be a Tama.",
  "JackalHadouHoSkCandidate": "Candidate set: {0}. Approach within 1.5 tiles for 1.5s next round.",
  "JackalHadouHoSkSuccess": "{0} is now your Tama.",
  "JackalHadouHoLoaded": "Loaded! Your next shot is a super beam.",
  "JackalHadouHo.DirectionDetect": "Move briefly in your firing direction. Beam charges right after.",

  "Tama": "Tama",
  "TamaInfo": "Sidekick of the Wave Cannon Jackal — press Kill on your owner to load them for a super beam",
  "TamaInfoLong": "(<#00b4eb>Jackal</color>):\n<size=80%>Load your Wave Cannon Jackal for a super beam — and inherit the cannon if they fall.\n_____________________________________\nDifficulty: ★★☆☆☆\n\n[Skills]\n・<b><color=#00b4eb>Load</color></b>\nPress your Kill button on your owner to load them, enabling their super beam. When the beam fires, you are consumed. While loaded, you teleport alongside your owner.\n\n[Condition]\nIf your owner dies or loses their role, you are promoted to a new Wave Cannon Jackal.\n\n<i>Ready on your mark.</i></size>",
  "TamaCanLoad": "Tama Can Load Owner",
  "TamaLoadCooldown": "Tama Load Cooldown",
  "TamaLoaded": "Loaded! Your owner can now fire a super beam.",

  "ForceFielder": "Force Fielder",
  "ForceFielderInfo": "Toggle a force field that repels nearby players; your speed drops while it's active",
  "ForceFielderInfoLong": "(<#8cffff>Crewmates</color>):\n<size=80%>Deploy a force field that pushes away anyone who enters it — at the cost of your own speed.\n_____________________________________\nDifficulty: ★★☆☆☆\n\n[Skills]\n・<b><color=#8cffff>Force Field</color></b>\nPet to toggle the force field on or off. While active, any player who enters the field is pushed outward. Your movement speed is reduced while the field is active. The field deactivates automatically at the start of a meeting.\n\n<i>Back off.</i></size>",
  "ForceFielder.FieldRadius": "Field Radius",
  "ForceFielder.SpeedMultiplier": "Speed Multiplier While Active",
  "ForceFielder.PropelForce": "Eject Margin",
  "ForceFielder.ActivationCooldown": "Activation Cooldown",
  "ForceFielder.EjectOnActivation": "Eject players inside when field activates",
  "ForceFielder.EjectOnActivation.Description": "OFF: players caught inside the field at activation are trapped (can't move but stay inside). ON: all players inside at activation are ejected once.",
  "ForceFielder.FieldOn": "Force Field: ON",
  "ForceFielder.FieldOff": "Force Field: OFF",
  "ForceFielder.Cooldown": "Force Field is on cooldown",

  "SantaClaus": "SantaClaus",
  "SantaClausInfo": "Complete tasks to gather presents, then enter the chimney vent to deliver them; reach the delivery target to win",
  "SantaClausInfoLong": "(<#ffab1b>Neutrals</color>):\n<size=80%>Gather presents through tasks and deliver them via the chimney vent — spread enough gifts to win.\n_____________________________________\nDifficulty: ★★☆☆☆\n\n[Skills]\n・<b><color=#ffab1b>Present Delivery</color></b>\nComplete tasks to collect presents (one per task). A random vent is marked as the chimney — enter it while holding a present to deliver. Each delivery grants a random alive player an add-on, and the chimney moves to a new vent afterward.\n\n[Win Condition]\nDeliver the required number of presents. With Add-Win Mode on, you win alongside whoever wins instead of winning outright.\n\n<i>Spreading joy, one delivery at a time.</i></size>",
  "SantaClausWinGivePresentCount": "Deliveries To Win",
  "SantaClausMaxHavePresent": "Max Presents Held At Once",
  "SantaClausAddWinMode": "Add-Win Mode (else Solo Win)",
  "SantaClausGiftAddon": "Gift Random Addon On Delivery",
  "SantaClausCollect": "Complete tasks to get presents.",
  "SantaClausDeliver": "Deliver via chimney:",
  "SantaClausAbilityText": "Chimney",
  "SantaClausMeetingMsg0": "I dropped a present in {0}!",
  "SantaClausMeetingMsg1": "A small surprise was left in {0}.",
  "SantaClausMeetingMsg2": "Did you spot something shiny in {0}?",
  "SantaGiftAddonMessage": "You received a gift from SantaClaus: {0}",

  "MassMedia": "Mass Media",
  "MassMediaInfo": "Mark a target; if someone kills them, self-report the body and guess the killer to win",
  "MassMediaInfoLong": "(<#ffab1b>Neutrals</color>):\n<size=80%>Mark a target, wait for them to be killed, self-report the body, then correctly identify the killer to win.\n_____________________________________\nDifficulty: ★★★☆☆\n\n[Skills]\n・<b><color=#ffab1b>Mark</color></b>\nUse the kill button to mark a target — no kill occurs. Your vision narrows when near them. When they are killed by someone, their position is revealed to you.\n\n・<b><color=#ffab1b>Guess</color></b>\nSelf-report your marked target's body to enter Guess Mode. Vote for who you believe killed them. Guess correctly to win; guess wrong and you die.\n\n<i>The story is only as good as the source.</i></size>",
  "MassMediaBlackVisionAmount": "Vision While Near Target",
  "MassMediaMeetingTargetReset": "Reset Target on Meeting",
  "MassMediaCanSeeKillFlash": "See Kill Flash on Target Death",
  "MassMediaCriminalProfile": "Criminal Profile (Mark Suspects in Meeting)",
  "MassMediaTargetHUD": "Target: {0}",
  "MassMediaNoTarget": "No Target — use Kill to mark",
  "MassMediaGuessMode": "Guess Mode: vote for the killer!",
  "MassMediaChance": "Vote for who killed your target. Wrong guess = you die.",
  "MassMediaGuessCanceled": "Guess canceled.",
  "MassMediaGuessCorrect": "Correct! The scoop goes live!",
  "MassMediaGuessWrong": "Wrong target... the story falls apart.",

  /* ==============================
    Faction Information
  ============================== */

  "CovenInfoDescription": "The Coven is a Team of 1-4 people, after 3 meetings (amount replaced with hosts settings) a random Member of the Coven will gain the Necronomicon. With the Necronomicon, that Coven Member may kill normally and also has a stronger ability. After the Necronomicon was given to the first member, every meeting after will give it to another until all members of the Coven have it. Most roles in this faction are also Support oriented, meaning that they need Teamwork and coordination to work perfectly together.\n\nThe Necronomicon is an ability buff owned by a single member of the Coven. The Necronomicon goes to a different Coven member after every meeting, and for that round will buff their role's ability. Most Coven roles will state in their description what the Necronomicon buffs in their role.\n\n<size=50%>Credit to mystic_haze2 on Discord for writing the first paragraph</size>",
  "NeutralInfoDescription": "Neutrals do not belong to Crewmates or Impostors, and they win on their own terms. Each type of neutral wins in a different way. Neutrals work for themselves and have specific conditions depending on their role on how to win.\n\n<b>Neutral Benigns</b> win when their specific conditions are completed, each role having different conditions necessary to win. They do not trigger the game to end, meaning they must wait until the Crewmates, Impostors, Coven, or another Neutral to win the game and win along with them. \n\n<b>Neutral Evils</b> also have their own specific conditions to win, much like the Neutral Benigns. However, when they complete their objectives to win the game, they end the game and win without Crewmates, Coven, or Impostors- also called 'stealing the win'.\n\n<b>Neutral Killers</b> are neutrals who can kill, much like Impostors, but do not work with the Impostors. Most of the Neutral killers work on their own, although some can recruit other players to work with them. They win the game by killing off all the Impostors, Cremwates, Coven, and other Neutrals, until they are the only player remaining.\n\n<b>Neutral Pariah</b> roles are much like Neutral Benign roles, however their main objective is to make sure Crewmates do not win. If any team other than the Crewmates win, said Neutral Pariah role will win along with the winning team. They have special abilities to try and harm the crewmates.",

  /* ==============================
    Chaos Pot Support (Yaminabe)
  ============================== */
